\begin_layout Section
Open Economy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is monetary policy less or more effective in a small open economy? How does
 the exchange rate affect it?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the economy is opened up, a new variable is introduced (the exchange
 rate).
 The nominal exchange rate (local currency per $) is 
\begin_inset Formula $e$
\end_inset

 and the real exchange rate is 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{r}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The national accounting identity is then:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Y=C(r,e^{r})+I(r,e^{r})+G+X(r,e^{r})-IM(r,e^{r})
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Where 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is the exports, 
\begin_inset Formula $IM$
\end_inset

 is the imports and 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{r}$
\end_inset

 is the real exchange rate, given by price level adjustment:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
e^{r}=\frac{CPI^{\$}}{CPI^{local}}e
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{r}$
\end_inset

 goes up, 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 increases and 
\begin_inset Formula $IM$
\end_inset

 decreases, leading to an increase of 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the nominal exchange goes up, local prices goes up (goods are mroe expensive)
 and the inflation goes up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
UIP
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In an open economy, the returns on all the local bonds and foreign bonds
 are equalized.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Adding expectations and a small countrhy risk rate (
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

), for discrete time:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
1+i_{t}-\rho=\frac{E_{t}(e_{t+1})}{e_{t}}(1+i_{t}^{\$})
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In continuous time:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
e_{t}\approx E_{t}(e_{t+1})+i_{t}^{\$}-(i_{t}-\rho)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Meaning, the domestic bonds (
\begin_inset Formula $i_{t}$
\end_inset

) and the foreign ones (
\begin_inset Formula $i^{\$})$
\end_inset

 have the same expected return.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
